      "content": "A living constitution approach, also known as constitutional evolution, accepts that the Constitution is a dynamic document that can adapt to changing societal needs and values. Proponents argue that this approach provides a more modern and flexible understanding of the Constitution, allowing it to evolve with the times. By contrast, originalism's strict textualism can indeed seem arbitrary, limiting the judiciary's role to simply reading the 18th-century meaning of the Constitution, rather than considering its relevance to contemporary issues.",
